Content:: Bjørn Inge Mo (16 March 1968 – 10 July 2022) was a Norwegian politician. A member of the Labour Party, he was mayor of Kåfjord from 2003 to 2015 and served in the Sámi Parliament of Norway from 2017 to 2020.[1] Mo died on 10 July 2022 at the age of 54.[2]  This article about a Norwegian politician born in the 1960s is a stub.
